.TH "polyglot\-agents" "7" "" "Runtime Documentation" "Polyglot Devcontainers"
.SH NAME
polyglot\-agents \- operating guidance for coding agents in the
container
.SH PURPOSE
This page describes how an agent should behave inside
polyglot\-devcontainers.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page before making changes or declaring work complete.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
man polyglot
man polyglot\-task\-contract
task maintainer:up
task maintainer:task \-\- ci
task maintainer:git \-\- status \-\-short \-\-branch
task maintainer:gh \-\- run view 24285030079
task image:discover
task image:pin \-\- \-\-write
task image:verify
task ci
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
Agent defaults:
.IP " 1." 4
gather context from local runtime docs and the workspace
.IP " 2." 4
pull and use the published maintainer container as the only valid agent
execution environment
.IP " 3." 4
enter that environment through the official Dev Containers CLI against
the checked\-in maintainer devcontainer definition
.IP " 4." 4
follow the task contract
.IP " 5." 4
inspect artifacts when doing security or dependency work
.IP " 6." 4
use \f[CR]task image:discover\f[R] before changing published image base
references
.IP " 7." 4
use an explicit write step such as
\f[CR]task image:pin \-\- \-\-write\f[R]
.IP " 8." 4
verify the published images with \f[CR]task image:verify\f[R]
.IP " 9." 4
classify critical published\-image findings as either
\f[CR]repo\-fixable\f[R] or \f[CR]upstream residual\f[R]
.IP "10." 4
prefer the latest upstream\-supported binary release for third\-party
tools and do not self\-build vendor tools only to suppress scanner
output
.IP "11." 4
use the smallest change that solves the real problem
.SH OUTPUTS / ARTIFACTS
Agents should treat \f[CR].artifacts/scans/\f[R] as a first\-class
source of evidence.
.PP
Published image maintenance also writes evidence under:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]base\-image\-report.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]base\-image\-report.md\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image\-security/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image\-security/residual\-risk.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image\-security/residual\-risk.md\f[R]
.SH COMMON FAILURES
.IP \(bu 2
relying on memory instead of reading the local contract
.IP \(bu 2
using host tooling as proof of success
.IP \(bu 2
rebuilding the maintainer container on the host when the published GHCR
image is sufficient
.IP \(bu 2
running repository workflows on the host instead of the maintainer
container
.IP \(bu 2
skipping \f[CR]task ci\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
ignoring generated artifacts after dependency or security tasks
.IP \(bu 2
editing published image base references without an explicit discovery
report
.IP \(bu 2
changing pins without a deliberate write step
.IP \(bu 2
treating the latest upstream\-supported vendor binary as
repository\-owned code that should be privately rebuilt to hide a
scanner finding
.SH GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 2
start with \f[CR]man polyglot\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
prefer validated starter workflows over improvised ones
.IP \(bu 2
keep changes aligned with the repository\(cqs security\-first posture
.IP \(bu 2
use the Knowledge layer when judgment is needed, not just mechanics
.IP \(bu 2
treat the published images as a separate maintenance lane: discover,
pin, verify, then scan
.IP \(bu 2
use \f[CR]task maintainer:up\f[R],
\f[CR]task maintainer:task \-\- ...\f[R],
\f[CR]task maintainer:git \-\- ...\f[R], and
\f[CR]task maintainer:gh \-\- ...\f[R] when you need to enter the
maintainer lane from the host
.IP \(bu 2
for HTTPS remotes, let \f[CR]task maintainer:git \-\- ...\f[R] bridge
credentials into a single container\-side Git command instead of pushing
from the host or persisting secrets in the container
.IP \(bu 2
for GitHub API and Actions work, let
\f[CR]task maintainer:gh \-\- ...\f[R] inject \f[CR]GH_TOKEN\f[R] /
\f[CR]GITHUB_TOKEN\f[R] or a host\-derived token into one
container\-side command instead of logging \f[CR]gh\f[R] into the
container
.IP \(bu 2
if the maintainer container cannot execute the workflow, fix the
maintainer container rather than falling back to the host
.IP \(bu 2
on Windows worktrees, use
\f[CR]git worktree add \-\-relative\-paths\f[R] if you want the Dev
Containers CLI to mount the Git common dir for container\-side Git
.IP \(bu 2
for published\-image CVEs, fix repo\-owned causes first: stale base
images, stale distro packages, stale pinned versions, and missing
verification
.IP \(bu 2
if a critical remains in the latest upstream\-supported release of a
managed binary such as \f[CR]trivy\f[R], \f[CR]gitleaks\f[R], or
\f[CR]task\f[R], record it as upstream residual risk and keep the
upstream artifact
